cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

The paper deals with a random access technique designed for satellite return links, which involves multiple transmission and interference cancellation. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of autocorrelation to localise replicas of a same packet so as to coherently combine them, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses the impact of signal misalignment in terms of residual timing offsets and phase shifts, which could be relevant to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper assesses the performance of the technique through simulations, which could be related to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
